##Diary of the siege of Wuhan | Day 40

Techread

Features, Lanxi, founder of zhulu.com  , focuses on in-depth observations and business reviews of Internet startups, new media, and subcultures.

Wuhan Wind Knife Frost Sword recently, often fall cold rain, all the scenery in the field of vision are immersed in muddy dark.

The number of newly diagnosed cases also started to drop unexpectedly. It should have reached the final stage of cleaning up. If there is no accident, the curve will no longer have the opportunity to go up. Judging from the few comments made by the local community, the mood of the public has eased a lot, i believe the closing bell is about to ring.

After yesterday's diary was sent out, many people wanted to send me a coke express. Thank you, Ha. I really can't bear such a little pain. I can even swallow a few mouthfuls of vegetables when I eat now, and my health has gone straight up, try to hold on to the reins of a blessing in disguise.

NASA satellite images are said to show that the air pollution over the cities centered on northern China is almost gone compared to January, when winds blew away the purplish red nitrogen dioxide, the whole land seemed to permeate.

It was an unexpected benefit of a sudden cessation of industrial activity -- A price to be paid, whether or not it eventually became a brief interlude in a long history, a magnificent experience for the one billion, four hundred million of them.

The History Channel Documentary "the world after people" was mentioned, which assumes that in a future after people suddenly disappeared, how long would it take for the traces of human civilization to disappear?

If not fastidious about visual effects, the film's Wild Earth is actually very interesting, with vines crawling all over the wire bridges, dams crumbling in seconds, and concrete ruins turning to dust, there's a pack of wolves on the Manhattan I. .

Scientists say that if you exclude man made radioactive material, the oldest evidence humans have of their existence will be the footprints they left on the surface of the Armstrong, yes, when all the great engineering on earth is doomed to vanish into thin air, the record of the astronauts'visit to another celestial body becomes one of the few remaining clues to civilization.

Of course, anti-industrialists always lack some "human touch" . For example, they tend to think that human beings are the virus of the Earth, and the earth will be better without human beings, it avoids the fact that good and bad are the standard invented by human beings. The Earth Has No judgment of likes and dislikes. No human being's earth is worth no more than ten million stars in the universe, even if it has fresh air.

I mean, the world can be fucked up at times, but it's also an important quality in the world, it's always losing something and creating something else, and everybody comes into the world, or as a meteor across the sky, even if no one saw, the sky will remember it came.

As Albert Camus wrote in "return to Tipazza" : "In the depths of winter, I know at last that there is an unconquerable summer in me. "

Take care of the flame in your heart. It is the candle of knowledge, the torch through the cave, the shadow that lights the night, the Red Sun that nourishes life, the passion, the Circle of Life.
